com.link_intersystems.lang.reflect

Class Constructor2<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.link_intersystems.lang.reflect.Member2<Constructor<T>>
      • com.link_intersystems.lang.reflect.Constructor2<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Member

    public class Constructor2<T>
extends Member2<Constructor<T>>
    A Constructor2 is an extension of the standard java Constructor. It adapts the standard java Constructor to the abstract Invokable api and adds additional methods useful when resolving an applicable constructor at runtime.
    Since:
    1.0.0;
    Author:
    Ren√© Link [rene.link@link- intersystems.com]

      • getSignature

        public Signature getSignature()
        Specified by:
        getSignature in class Member2<Constructor<T>>
        Returns:
        a Signature that represents this constructor. Clients might use the Signature to compare it to others. The returned Signature's attributes are
        • name
        • parameter types
        Two Signatures are equal if these attributes are equal. Therefore two constructor signatures can be equal even if they do not belong to the same declaring class (e.g. same class name in different packages).
        Since:
        1.0.0;
